\pard\qc\f0\fs36 AI-Based Plant Disease Identification Application\par
\pard\fs24\par
\pard\f1\fs24\b 1. Project Overview\b0\par
This repository contains a prototype application for multilingual plant disease diagnosis. The application uses a Vue.js frontend and a FastAPI backend. The architecture is intended to support image-based and text-based diagnosis, multilingual output, and feedback capture for future model improvement.\par
\pard\fs24\par
\b 2. System Architecture\b0\par
The application has two main layers:\par
\pard\li720\fi-720\fs20\bullet Frontend: Vue 3 web application served by Vite.\par
\bullet Backend: FastAPI REST API that receives diagnosis requests, performs model inference and translation, and manages feedback.\par
\bullet Data persistence: SQLAlchemy models define diagnosis and feedback records.\par
\pard\fs24\par
\b 3. Frontend Details\b0\par
\pard\fi720\fs20\b Entry point: \b0 `frontend/src/main.js`\par
\pard\fi1440\fs20\bullet Creates the Vue app and configures router paths:\par
  \pard\fi2160\bullet `/` -> Home\par
  \bullet `/diagnose` -> DiagnosisPage\par
  \bullet `/results/:id` -> Results page\par
  \bullet `/history` -> History page\par
\pard\fi720\fs20\bullet `frontend/src/App.vue` wraps the router and page layout.\par
\pard\fs20\bullet `frontend/src/services/api.js` defines the API client and backend calls:\par
  \pard\fi2160\bullet `diagnoseImage()` sends image files and selected language to `/api/v1/diagnose`.\par
  \bullet `diagnoseText()` sends symptom description and language to `/api/v1/diagnose/text`.\par
  \bullet `getLanguages()` retrieves supported languages from `/api/v1/languages`.\par
  \bullet `submitFeedback()` posts user feedback to `/api/v1/feedback`.\par
\pard\fs24\par
\b Diagnosis UI\b0\par
\pard\fi720\fs20\bullet `frontend/src/pages/DiagnosisPage.vue` contains the main diagnosis interface.\par
  \pard\fi2160\bullet Two tabs: image upload and symptom text input.\par
  \bullet Output language selector is present in both tabs using `selectedLanguage`.\par
  \bullet The user can optionally specify plant type.\par
  \bullet When the user submits, the page calls the backend with the chosen language.\par
\pard\fs24\par
\b Results and History\b0\par
\pard\fi720\fs20\bullet `frontend/src/pages/Results.vue` displays diagnosis results.\par
\bullet `frontend/src/pages/History.vue` displays historical diagnosis records and target language.\par
\pard\fs24\par
\b 4. Backend Details\b0\par
\pard\fs20\b Entry point: \b0 `src/api/main.py`\par
\pard\fi720\fs20\bullet FastAPI application with CORS support.\par
\bullet Endpoints:\par
  \pard\fi1440\bullet `GET /health` - health check.\par
  \bullet `POST /api/v1/diagnose` - image diagnosis endpoint.\par
  \bullet `POST /api/v1/diagnose/text` - text diagnosis endpoint.\par
  \bullet `GET /api/v1/languages` - returns supported languages.\par
  \bullet `POST /api/v1/feedback` - accepts feedback records.\par
\pard\fs20\bullet The current implementation returns placeholder responses for both diagnosis endpoints (`Pipeline implementation pending`).\par
\pard\fs24\par
\b 5. Configuration\b0\par
\pard\fi720\fs20\bullet `src/config.py` defines application settings using Pydantic Settings.\par
  \pard\fi1440\bullet API host and port\par
  \bullet Database URL and connection settings\par
  \bullet LLM configuration including model, temperature, and local API URL\par
  \bullet Vector DB settings for Chroma\par
  \bullet Supported languages: `en,hi,ta,te,ka,ml,kn,mr,gu,bn`\par
  \bullet Vision model settings, including default `efficientnet_v2` and model path.\par
\pard\fs24\par
\b 6. Multilingual Handling\b0\par
\pard\fs20\bullet Supported languages are defined in both the frontend and backend.\par
\bullet The frontend exposes an `Output Language` drop-down on the diagnosis page.\par
\bullet Selected language is sent as a request parameter to the backend.\par
\bullet `src/multilingual/translator.py` contains a translator stub with supported language codes and a `translate()` method.\par
\pard\fi720\fs20\bullet `Translator.translate()` currently returns the original text and logs translation actions; it is a placeholder for integration with a real translation service.\par
\pard\fs20\bullet The backend language endpoint `/api/v1/languages` returns the same supported language mapping.\par
\pard\fs24\par
\b 7. Vision Model and PlantVillage Connection\b0\par
\pard\fs20\bullet `src/vision/model.py` defines `VisionModel`, a wrapper around PyTorch torchvision models.\par
  \pard\fi1440\bullet Supports `efficientnet_v2_s` and `vit_b16`.\par
  \bullet Loads pretrained weights from torchvision and replaces the final classifier head to support `num_classes=38`.\par
  \bullet Provides a `predict()` method returning logits and probabilities.\par
\pard\fs20\bullet The repository contains no dataset files. The design assumes a dataset such as the PlantVillage leaf disease dataset would be used for training.\par
\pard\fs20\bullet `PlantVillage` is mentioned in README acknowledgments, but there is no integrated dataset loader or training script in this repository.\par
\pard\fs24\par
\b 8. Training and Detection\b0\par
\pard\fs20\bullet This codebase currently has no explicit training pipeline, no `train.py`, and no labeled dataset loader.\par
\bullet `VisionModel` is prepared for classification, not detection.\par
\bullet There is no object detection module in the repository; only classification inference is architected.\par
\pard\fs24\par
\b 9. Database Models\b0\par
\pard\fs20\bullet `src/database/models.py` defines ORM models using SQLAlchemy:\par
  \pard\fi1440\bullet `DiagnosisRecord` stores diagnosis data, detected disease, confidence, symptoms, severity, recommendations, and target language.\par
  \bullet `FeedbackRecord` stores user feedback and notes for RLHF-style improvement.\par
\pard\fs24\par
\b 10. LLM Reasoning\b0\par
\pard\fs20\bullet `src/llm/engine.py` defines `DiagnosisEngine`, a stub for LLM-based reasoning.\par
\bullet It is designed to generate diagnostic text and recommendations from disease name, confidence, and symptoms.\par
\bullet Current implementation returns a placeholder message and does not call a real LLM.\par
\pard\fs24\par
\b 11. Frontend Language Option\b0\par
\pard\fs20\bullet In the current frontend application, the language selector exists on the diagnosis page in both image and text modes.\par
\bullet If the welcome page appears, you must click \b Start Diagnosis\b0 or visit `http://localhost:5173/diagnose` to access the real UI.\par
\pard\fs24\par
\b 12. How to Run\b0\par
\pard\fs20\bullet Backend:\par
  \pard\fi1440\bullet `python -m venv venv`\par
  \bullet `venv\\Scripts\\activate` (Windows) or `source venv/bin/activate` (macOS/Linux)\par
  \bullet `python -m pip install --upgrade pip setuptools wheel`\par
  \bullet `python -m pip install --prefer-binary -r requirements.txt`\par
  \bullet `uvicorn src.api.main:app --reload`\par
\pard\fs20\bullet Frontend:\par
  \pard\fi1440\bullet `cd frontend`\par
  \bullet `npm install`\par
  \bullet `npm run dev`\par
\pard\fs24\par
\b 13. Points\b0\par
\pard\fs20\bullet Explain the two-tier architecture: frontend UI and backend API.\par
\bullet Describe how the frontend selects a language and sends it to the backend.\par
\bullet Describe the placeholder nature of the backend diagnosis endpoints and the need for a real model inference/LLM integration.\par
\bullet Explain that `VisionModel` is classifier-focused, using pretrained torchvision models adapted for 38 disease classes.\par
\bullet Clarify that the multilingual system is structured but not fully implemented: translation stubs are in `src/multilingual/translator.py`, and supported languages are exposed through the API.\par
\bullet Mention that PlantVillage is referenced as the intended training dataset, but actual dataset loading and training scripts are absent from the repo.\par
\pard\fs24\par
\b 14. Summary\b0\par
This repository is a prototype that demonstrates the skeleton of a plant disease diagnosis system with multilingual capabilities. It includes a working Vue frontend, a FastAPI backend API, and model wrappers, but it still needs a complete inference pipeline, dataset integration, and training code to be fully production ready.\par
}
